Cell.Text: Isn't it amazing?
G|Just think. We're the first to set foot here in thousands of years.
G|I can't wait to see what's inside!

[S] <<Shared>> Alduin's Wall is one of the lost glories of the Blades. Where they recorded all they knew of Alduin and his return. Part history, part prophecy. | Its location has been lost for centuries, but I've found it again. | Not lost, you see, just forgotten. The Blades archives held so many secrets... I was only able to save a few scraps...
G|Patience. Give me a moment and I'll explain everything.

Node.Caption: MQ203EsbernBlockingTopic

Cell.Text: [S] G|Ah. Of course. Not everyone has an appreciation for the artistic wonders of the world. | Let me see if I can find the right panel...
[S] G|Ah. Of course. Not everyone has an appreciation for the artistic wonders of the world.

Node.Caption: MQ203EsbernCutToTheChase: I just want to know how to defeat Alduin.

Cell.Text: G|Ah. Thank you! Excellent. Now... where were we?

Node.Caption: MQ203EsbernContinue: It is. Carry on.

Cell.Text: S|Have you ever heard of such a thing? A Shout that can knock a dragon out of the sky?
Have you ever heard of a Shout that can knock a dragon out of the sky?
G|Let's go see if Esbern's right about Alduin's Wall.
G|After you, Dragonborn.
I know the area of the Reach that Esbern's talking about. Near what's now known as Karthspire, in the Karth River canyon. | We can meet you there, or all travel together, your call.

Node.Caption: MQ203DelphineBlockingTopic: What did you need?

Cell.Text: I was afraid you were going to say that. | I guess there's nothing for it. We'll have to ask the Greybeards for help. | I hoped to avoid involving them in this, but we have no other choice.

Node.Caption: MQ203DelphineRemansWallA1: No, I've never heard of anything like that.

Cell.Text: You're probably right. I was hoping to avoid having to involve them in this, but it seems we have no choice.

Node.Caption: MQ203DelphineRemansWallA2: The Greybeards might know.

Cell.Text: [S] G|<<Shared>> Right. Good thing they've already let you into their little cult. Not likely they'd help Esbern or me if we came calling. | We'll look around Sky Haven Temple and see what else the old Blades might have left for us. It's a better hideout than I could have hoped for. | Talos guard you.

Node.Caption: MQ203DelphineRemansWallB2: I'll ask Arngeir if he knows what Shout they used.

Cell.Text: Really? He's safe? Where is he?

Node.Caption: MQ203FoundEsbernTopic: I found Esbern.

Cell.Text: He's here in Riverwood. Right outside.
[S] G|Mara's mercy, then he's safe! Come on, we have a lot to discuss.
[S] G|What? You left him on his own? With the Thalmor after him? Go make sure he's safe and bring him here!

Node.Caption: MQ203FoundEsbernA1: He's on his way.

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> If they had their way, you'd do nothing but sit up on their mountain with them and talk to the sky, or whatever it is they do. | The Greybeards are so afraid of power that they won't use it. | Think about it. Have they tried to stop the civil war, or done anything about Alduin? | No. And they're afraid of you, of your power. | Trust me, there's no need to be afraid. Think of Tiber Septim. Do you think he'd have founded the Empire if he'd listened to the Greybeards?

Node.Caption: MQ203DelphineRemansWallB1: What do you have against the Greybeards?

Cell.Text: Only if you don't know how to use it. All the great heroes have had to learn to use their power. | Those that shrank from their destiny... well, you've never heard of them, have you? | And there are the villains - those that misused their power. There's always a choice, and there's always a risk. | But if you live in fear of what might go wrong, you'll end up doing nothing. Like the Greybeards up on their mountain.

Node.Caption: MQ203DelphineRemansWallC1: The Greybeards may have a point. Power is dangerous.

Cell.Text: Good. The Greybeards can teach you a lot, but don't let them turn you away from your destiny. | You're Dragonborn, and you're the only one who can stop Alduin. Don't forget it.

Node.Caption: MQ203DelphineRemansWallC2: Don't worry. I'm not afraid of my own power.

Cell.Text: [S] G|<<Shared>> Right. Good thing they've already let you into their little cult. Not likely they'd help Esbern or me if we came calling. | We'll look around Sky Haven Temple and see what else the old Blades might have left for us. It's a better hideout than I could have hoped for. | Talos guard you.

Node.Caption: MQ203DelphineRemansWallD1: I'd better go see what Arngeir knows about this Shout.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Certainly. The Ratway can be a bit confusing to the uninitiated. Stay close.

Node.Caption: MQ203EsbernRatwayTopic: Do you know the way out of here?

Cell.Text: [S] The Akaviri blood seal can only be opened with the right kind of blood. Your blood, Dragonborn.
We should proceed cautiously. There's no telling what traps and wards the ancient Blades may have set.
The entrance must be past the Forsworn camp. Look for a canyon or cave entrance into the Karthspire.
How do we get to Sky Haven Temple?
Ah, yes. The entrance seems to be near what's now known as the Karthspire. We'll have to see what we find when we arrive.

Node.Caption: MQ203EsbernKarthspireTopic: How do we find the entrance to Sky Haven Temple?

Cell.Text: [S] G|Very well. Delphine and I will wait for you there if we arrive first. But don't delay. Alduin grows stronger with each passing day.
[S] G|Your call. Might be safer to travel separately - attract less attention that way. | Don't worry, I'll get Esbern there in one piece. We'll wait for you near Karthspire. Good luck.

Node.Caption: MQ203MeetAtKarthspireTopic: I'll meet you at Karthspire.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Always. Let's go see if we can find this Sky Haven Temple.

Node.Caption: MQ203KarthspireTravelTogether: Let's travel there together. Are you ready to go?

Cell.Text: From Riverwood? The road south through Falkreath is the most direct route. | Or you could catch the carriage from Whiterun to Markarth and then approach from the west. | Either way, the Reach is wild country these days. The Forsworn are everywhere. Best be careful.

Node.Caption: MQ203KarthspireBestWay: What's the best way to get there?

Cell.Text: [S] G|We'll meet you there. Be careful. That part of the Reach is rough country these days.

Node.Caption: MQ203KarthspireWalkAway

Cell.Text: Yes, exactly. Well, I think so. It's certainly our best hope. The ancient Blades remembered much Akaviri dragonlore that has now been forgotten.

Node.Caption: MQ203EsbernAlduinsWallHowToDefeat: So you think Alduin's Wall will tell us how to defeat Alduin?

Cell.Text: [S] G|This is what I've been trying to explain. It's in Sky Haven Temple, an ancient Blades sanctuary, hidden deep in the crags of the Reach. | That's where we'll find Alduin's Wall.

Node.Caption: MQ203EsbernAlduinsWallWhere: Where can we find Alduin's Wall?
